                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17037800" author="jensg" created="Sun, 16 Feb 2020 12:13:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marked critical since it blocks the CI on Github.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17053979" author="jensg" created="Sat, 7 Mar 2020 10:42:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17055423" author="janosvitok" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2020 22:15:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After fixing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5120&quot; title=&quot;TypeError: fs.copyFileSync is not a function&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-5120&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-5120&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, this bug appears again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see two solutions here: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. block byebug &amp;gt;=11.1: add line to /lib/rb/thrift.gemspec: add_dependency &quot;~&amp;gt;11.0&quot; , &quot;&amp;lt;11.1&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
   the problem here is that 11.1 brings support for ruby 2.7 which is useful.&lt;br/&gt;
2. upgrade ruby to at least 2.4. use &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.brightbox.com/docs/ruby/ubuntu/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;brightbox ppa&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I prefer 2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch provided in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/2054&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/2054&lt;/a&gt; commit e59d0656&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17055681" author="jensg" created="Tue, 10 Mar 2020 08:14:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree, will review. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
